  "text": "The authors did not discuss exclusion criteria in this paper. However it is well established that any type of systemic inflammation, autoimmune disorders, and malignant or chronic illnesses may affect inflammatory biomarkers and hormone levels [CITATION_1] . Also obesity is related to elevated serum levels of some inflammatory markers, such as leptin, TNF-, and CRP [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Because of high prevalence of these conditions, we believe that these situations may have a role in the results of the paper by C. B. Papini et al. [CITATION_4] .",
